column17:
The following post uses a distract tactic by discussing an irrelevant topic (Netflix and a TV show) in the midst of a coordinated campaign focusing on political issues:

@netflix Bring back 1899! :)

This post is out of place in the context of the other tweets which are focused on criticizing the Tory party, corruption, and other political issues. The mention of a TV show does not contribute to the campaign's message and can be seen as an attempt to distract or divert attention away from the main topic of discussion.

column11:
